The paper discusses a model for predicting the publication productivity of researchers, which is a topic related to digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and social networks (cs.SI). The model is based on analyzing the distribution of researchers' publications, which can also be related to computational complexity (cs.CR) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
